text: Lisa has been the worst travel planner we have ever had to work with. To begin, she can’t communicate clearly or even spell words correctly, so almost all her interactions with us were incredibly hard to read and understand. Next, she kept emailing us the wrong dates and times for almost everything on the trip. You name it, she messed it up, from flights to shuttles to hotel info. It was unbelievably confusing and frustrating to have to keep clarifying and working through misinformation. Additionally, she has an excuse for everything and can’t take ownership of her mistakes. We never received an apology for one of her many errors. She was pushy, illiterate, lazy, and entitled. I would never recommend her to anyone and have no idea how she has received any positive reviews. This has been a horrible experience for all of us. There were so many problems and we would have been a thousand times better off putting the trip together ourselves. Do yourself the biggest favor and never bring your business to this irresponsible girl.

resp.text: Hello Sarah J.   My sincerest apologies for your bad experience with a travel planner.  But, it isn't me!  I went through all my files today looking for someone with your name and I don't have any client fitting your name.  I also communicate very clearly and am diligent in ensuring I have the correct information for my clients.  I would love to help you if you have travel needs and prove to you that I am actually excellent at my job.  It is sad to me that there are travel planners who aren't proficient at their job.  I am so sorry for your experience.  In addition I am a woman of 60 years not a "girl" with over 20 years in the business.  Whenever I have made a mistake, I always take responsibility for it and make it right.  As I said, you are welcome to reach out to me personally  and I would happily ensure you have a great experience.

name: Kayla Shelnutt
text: I reached out to Jamie several weeks ago to discuss booking a honeymoon in April of 2020. I originally filled out all the appropriate fields online and a few days passed and we never heard from anyone. No- problem. So my fiancé and I sat down to call and see if we could get the ball rolling. Our initial encounter with her was a little uneasy. She made up every excuse under the sun as to why she had been in contact with us and that she didn’t have enough staff to adequately return calls in a timely manner. We talked back and fourth via email. She didn’t act like she wanted to help us narrow down our search and advise us on where we could go with what we were wanting to spend. She was very adamant about us narrowing down where we wanted to go and to get back with her. I kept telling her we needed her help, that’s why we reached out to a travel agency! I threatened at one point- to use another travel agency if she didn’t want to help me. Oh at that point the emails came flooding in and she put fourth a little bit more effort. So fast forward to yesterday afternoon. I had a few minutes before getting kids off the bus so I ran to the Albertville location. When I got there I was somewhat greeted by a blond headed lady, can’t remember her name. I told her that I was there to go ahead and book a honeymoon and that I have been speaking with a lady named Jamie. Jamie was on the phone with another customer which was totally fine. I let her know first off that I was crunching for time. She sat down at her desk and seemed extremely overwhelmed and had no clue where to start to help me. When I told her to have Jamie contact me when she got off the phone she looked at me and told me to calm down waving her hands at me like I was a complete idiot! She kept saying she was new and it came across that she was not capable of performing her job duties as helping me with what I came in to do. She also popped off with a “wow lady “ as I walked out. I received an email from Jamie maybe an hour after all of this happened. I explain to her that I was upset and pretty much what I’ve said here and got absolutely no response. I will be going above her head if somethings not done about it. Management needs to focus on better training for the travel agents at this location. Poor customer service and they need to work on respecting potential customers!!
